<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-14T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60131/77: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Estonia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-14T18:00:00-04:00">July 14, 1937—6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>46. Your No. 91, July 10, 1 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d202fn21">Not
                                    printed.</note> Estonian informal proposals<note n="22" xml:id="d202fn22">The Estonian informal proposals and comments
                                    relative to a reciprocal trade treaty were contained in despatch
                                    No. 180 (Diplomatic), May 27, from the Chargé in Estonia
                                    (611.60i31/74).</note> are being given careful study but it is
                                not probable that the Department will be in a position to submit its
                                comments with regard to them until several weeks hence.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>